    "monster": true,
    "notes": "0kg Undead, urban \"Walker\", #App: 1, Treasure: None. Life drain (2d6); armor 0; walks 10m/action; Morale +4. A shadow is a soul cursed so that only its shadow remains. It creeps along walls and floors, seemingly a shade cast by the play of darkness and light. However, it is a malicious spirit thirsting for the life force of hapless, unsuspecting mortals. Undead: immune to poison, disease, and suffocation. Incorporeal: immune to non-magical weapons. Immune to mind-affecting magic. On a successful attack, the shadow heals itself half the damage it dealt, rounded down. Any creature slain by a shadow rises as a shadow the following midnight, unless its body is cremated.",
